        content: "The present invention provides a personalized postpartum recovery trajectory modeling system that generates individualized recovery milestones and timelines based on pre-pregnancy fitness baseline data from continuous wearable monitoring, pregnancy wellness trajectory data, delivery type and complication profile, breastfeeding status, and support system characteristics. The system continuously tracks actual biometric recovery against personalized benchmarks and detects trajectory deviations that may indicate complications or suboptimal recovery.\n\nThe recovery model operates across four sequential recovery phases: an acute phase spanning zero to two weeks focused on safety metrics including bleeding patterns, vital sign normalization, pain management, and infection risk detection, an early recovery phase spanning two to six weeks focused on healing trajectory including physical recovery markers, sleep pattern stabilization, and hormonal adjustment, a restoration phase spanning six to twelve weeks focused on rebuilding including energy normalization, pelvic floor recovery, fitness return, and mood stability, and an optimization phase spanning three to twelve or more months focused on baseline return including hormonal normalization, cycle recovery, and future fertility factor monitoring.\n\nFor each phase, the system generates personalized milestone targets derived from the intersection of the user's specific delivery profile and her pre-delivery physiological baseline. Expected heart rate recovery timeline, expected HRV normalization trajectory, expected energy level restoration, and expected cycle return timing are all calibrated to the individual rather than population averages."
